
clj-pivot: a library to comfortably use Apache Pivot (http://pivot.apache.org) from Clojure

Example

(ns pivot.test
  (:require [hoeck.pivot :as pivot]
            [hoeck.pivot.components :as cm]))

(pivot/start)
(pivot/disp->
  (pivot/show (cm/boxpane (cm/push-button :data "Hello Pivot"))))

Demo

applet: http://www.turbojugend-cossebaude.de/demo.html
webstart: http://www.turbojugend-cossebaude.de/demo.jnlp
jar: http://www.turbojugend-cossebaude.de/demo.jar

Building clj-pivot.jar

> lein deps
> ant jar-clj-pivot


Getting Started with the demo applet

> lein deps
> ant jar-all
> java -jar demo.jar


Features:
 
 * apache pivot
   - rich set of widgets, see:
       http://pivot.apache.org/demos/kitchen-sink.html
     and
       http://pivot.apache.org/demos/component-explorer.html
   - clean, modern and consistent api
   - dynamic
   - deployable as Desktop Application or Applet
   - event-based collections for keeping widgets in sync with the model

 * using the pivot api from clojure
   - less java calls
   - convenient constructor functions
   - function level documentation

 * declarative GUI definition using s-expressions

 * traversable component tree

 * data-binding using clojure hashmaps


Limitations/Downsides

 * limited to one host window (will be resolved in the upcoming pivot 1.6 or 2.0)
 * closing that window will quit the clojure-repl too
 * long startup time when used as an applet
 * slower than swing (100% AWT-Canvas based)
 * non-native look and feel

Dependencies

 * clojure-1.2
 * pivot 1.5.1

